/// This covers the cost of spawning a new OpenClaw agent container via claw-spawner.
/// Similar to ZK_PROOF_GENERATION_FEE_WEI - a fixed fee regardless of spawn duration.
///
/// **DoS-bounded throughput:** Set to 0.10 RIT to cap container spawns per RIT held by
/// any single user at ~10. The faucet drip is ~1 RIT per user per period; this fee
/// makes container-spawn-spam economically uninteresting at the per-user level while
/// still keeping the headline product affordable for legitimate dApp users. Previous
/// value (0.01 RIT) allowed ~99 spawns per RIT — far above the product-level ceiling.
pub const PERSISTENT_AGENT_SPAWN_FEE_WEI: u128 = 100_000_000_000_000_000; // 0.10 ETH

